WEBVTT

00:00.959 --> 00:04.045
♪♪

00:43.293 --> 00:45.920
-Morning, James.
-We're around the corner.

00:45.962 --> 00:49.632
-What do we got?
-Uh, hijacked bus. Perp's in
the wind.

00:49.716 --> 00:51.968
-Anybody hurt?
-Uh, nobody hurt, nobody
robbed.

00:52.010 --> 00:55.180
-Well, that's good anyway.
-Any word on the, uh, Abby
situation?

00:55.263 --> 00:57.182
Yeah, still watchful waitin'.

00:57.265 --> 01:01.478
All's I can tell you, James, if
she's not pregnant,
explanation's elsewhere.

01:01.519 --> 01:03.646
I gave a good supply of sperm.

01:08.026 --> 01:10.278
What in the world happened here?

01:11.863 --> 01:14.824
-This one tells it best.
-This one?

01:14.908 --> 01:17.994
-Mrs. Prows, this is Detective
Medavoy.
-How do you do?

01:18.078 --> 01:21.748
-I think this may have been my
fault.
-Really?

01:21.790 --> 01:24.709
The driver had to go to
the lavatory for a minute...

01:24.793 --> 01:28.463
and after he got off the bus,
I said to the man beside me...

01:28.505 --> 01:31.591
that when I'm late, my cat
does his business on the carpet.

01:31.674 --> 01:34.511
And he asked me where I live
and I told him and he just
went to the front of the bus

01:34.511 --> 01:38.098
and got in the driver's seat
and away we went.

01:38.181 --> 01:41.601
Uh, did he have liquor on his
breath, seemed like he might
have been on drugs?

01:41.684 --> 01:43.645
Well, he did have liquor
on his breath.

01:43.686 --> 01:48.191
When we were sitting next
to each other, he was
singing to himself–
Italian serenades.

01:48.274 --> 01:50.276
But he was very quiet and
polite.

01:50.318 --> 01:52.278
What did he look like?

01:52.320 --> 01:55.990
He was tall and lumbering,
with white hair...

01:56.032 --> 01:58.451
and like he could
lose 30 pounds.

01:58.493 --> 02:01.037
All right, thanks for your help,
Mrs. Prows.

02:01.121 --> 02:04.165
He was driving fine until
he tried to take a
shortcut to my street.

02:04.249 --> 02:07.460
One of the passengers said
he'd seen the guy that stole
the bus...

02:07.502 --> 02:10.672
-drinking a few days ago at
the, uh, Alibi Lounge.
-MEDAVOY: Oh, yeah?

02:10.713 --> 02:13.758
Mother of God!
Look what he did to my bus!

02:13.842 --> 02:17.428
Sir, please. The driver.
Sector car picked him up.

02:17.512 --> 02:22.142
-What's you name, sir?
-John O'Neil. What in the hell
could have been in his mind?

02:22.142 --> 02:25.562
-It's wedged in pretty good.
-If you could try to collect
yourself, John...

02:25.645 --> 02:28.314
uh, then we could
take your statement,
what occurred.

02:28.314 --> 02:30.692
Can't even take a piss
in this city.

02:30.733 --> 02:36.489
I'm with you there.
Many's the occasion that
I've regretted my small
bladder capacity.

02:36.531 --> 02:38.491
Uh, I gotta call my dispatcher.

02:38.533 --> 02:40.994
Yeah, fine, go ahead.
Then we'll get your account.

02:44.622 --> 02:47.000
Be fair to yourself, Greg.
This guy gets back to you...

02:47.000 --> 02:49.752
you tell him you do
have a big semen output.

02:52.672 --> 02:55.717
♪♪

03:59.155 --> 04:02.158
♪♪

04:07.121 --> 04:10.250
So the bus driver
gave a description?

04:10.291 --> 04:12.001
All right. All right.
Don't come in.

04:12.001 --> 04:14.879
Go back to that bar the witness
talked about seeing him at.

04:14.963 --> 04:17.674
See if they can put a name
to the guy. All right.

04:17.757 --> 04:20.051
-Hey.
-Good morning.

04:21.261 --> 04:23.554
911. What, am I fired?

04:23.596 --> 04:27.058
I.A.B. flagged you for
running that license plate.

04:27.100 --> 04:30.561
Oh. So, do I explain
to the Rat Squad...

04:30.603 --> 04:33.314
or, uh, send 'em to
these F.B.I. guys or what?

04:33.398 --> 04:37.860
-F.B.I. doesn't want that.
He'll walk you through it.
-You're gonna explain to
I.A.B.?

04:39.570 --> 04:42.198
-Morning.
-Agents Kriegel and Kazmaier.

04:42.240 --> 04:45.368
I remember.
What's going on?

04:45.410 --> 04:49.247
Your Internal Affairs Bureau
is going to talk to you about
the plate you ran for Joe
Salvo.

04:49.330 --> 04:53.334
My boss says you don't want
to tell I.A.B. it was your
request, which I got no
problem with.

04:53.418 --> 04:57.964
-Who is gonna tell 'em?
-We don't want you to
cooperate with I.A.B.

04:58.047 --> 05:02.927
-Tends to piss 'em off.
-They think Salvo has a hook
in I.A.B.

05:02.969 --> 05:06.723
We'll give you one piece of
bad information for each of
your I.A.B. interviews...

05:06.806 --> 05:10.977
and we'll I.D. the bought agent
off which piece Salvo winds up
getting.

05:11.060 --> 05:13.146
Meanwhile, where am I
for running the plate?

05:14.272 --> 05:16.441
That will all be made right.

05:16.524 --> 05:19.444
You string out I.A.B.,
I'm off the street.

05:19.485 --> 05:22.447
I told you, your position will
be made totally right.

05:22.488 --> 05:25.783
Boss, no one can make that
right.

05:25.825 --> 05:29.495
Bobby, right now,
you're in the middle of things.

05:29.495 --> 05:33.291
Yeah, which is a lot of
double-talk for “bite the
pillow and take your
screwing.”

05:40.048 --> 05:42.592
Gotta talk to my boss.

05:47.930 --> 05:49.390
Absolutely.

05:51.267 --> 05:52.810
Absolutely.

05:58.149 --> 06:00.318
W-Was this thing
with Salvo ever real?

06:00.318 --> 06:05.323
They say on their bugs he
keeps saying “our guy.” “Our
guy this,” “Our guy says.”

06:05.323 --> 06:07.867
How does that put the guy
in with I.A.B.?

06:07.909 --> 06:10.828
Kriegel wouldn't quote why,
but he said they're sure about
that.

06:10.828 --> 06:12.872
So I get sat down?

06:12.997 --> 06:15.833
Not if they come up with
Salvo's man off your
first interview.

06:15.875 --> 06:19.420
Well, if you can't trust
your career with these guys,
who can you trust?

06:19.504 --> 06:22.131
Bobby.

06:24.217 --> 06:28.471
-Anyone you tell about this,
you didn't do any favor.
-I'm telling her.

06:28.554 --> 06:31.682
If they make her for
knowing, she'll be jammed
just to get her out of the
way.

06:31.682 --> 06:34.811
I'm telling Russell or I'm gonna
tell the truth up and down.

06:34.894 --> 06:38.481
And let 'em suspend me for
impeding their investigation.

06:38.523 --> 06:42.902
-Well, I wouldn't tell
anyone else.
-(Phone Rings)

06:47.115 --> 06:48.533
I'm sorry about this.

06:48.699 --> 06:51.202
Boss, I wish you would have
stood up for me better.

06:51.202 --> 06:56.207
-What could I have done?
-Yeah. That's what I can't
figure out.

07:08.219 --> 07:12.306
-(Sighs)
-Why'd the boss beep you?

07:12.390 --> 07:15.852
The Rat Squad's gonna land on me
for doing Salvo that solid.

07:15.935 --> 07:19.564
But you can tell I.A.B.
the F.B.I. asked you to do that.

07:19.605 --> 07:23.359
-No?
-Diane, you start going off
here...

07:23.401 --> 07:25.653
it's only gonna prove
Fancy's right not wanting me
to tell you.

07:27.947 --> 07:31.033
-How's it going?
-How's it going?

07:33.744 --> 07:38.082
-How's it going, Andy?
-Assault-rape, First Avenue
and Eighth.

07:38.124 --> 07:40.543
-Good morning.
-How's it going?

07:43.504 --> 07:46.090
Diane, you want to meet
Greg and James at the Alibi
Lounge?

07:46.090 --> 07:47.675
RUSSELL:
Sure.

08:06.777 --> 08:09.780
Ready.

08:09.822 --> 08:13.493
Do me a favor. Don't turn my
station off and then not say
nothing on the ride.

08:13.576 --> 08:16.370
-What are you talking about?
-Last while, I put on music,
you turn it off...

08:16.454 --> 08:18.456
then the whole ride,
you're looking out the window.

08:20.458 --> 08:21.709
Okay.

08:28.758 --> 08:30.843
(engine starts)

08:32.345 --> 08:34.639
Put on the radio.

08:34.680 --> 08:38.392
Or instead of keeping me
in the dark for what's
getting to be an insulting
period of time...

08:38.476 --> 08:40.520
-you could tell me what the
hell is going on.
-I can't, Andy.

08:40.603 --> 08:43.356
Is it domestic problems?
You'll be shocked, but I'm
acquainted with those.

08:43.439 --> 08:48.444
-Andy, please, you got to let
me up here.
-Sure. Consider yourself up.

08:50.112 --> 08:52.949
(radio: instrumental)

09:07.004 --> 09:10.591
-Fifteenth Squad detectives.
-What's going on, fellas?

09:10.675 --> 09:12.843
We're looking for someone
who frequents this bar.

09:12.885 --> 09:16.889
Yeah. White hair, over six
feet tall, uh, somewhat
heavyset.

09:18.683 --> 09:21.727
Yo, Vince.
Some guys from your squad.

09:21.769 --> 09:25.022
-Oh, boy.
-What's going on, gentlemen?

09:25.106 --> 09:27.108
-Hey, Vince.
-How's it going, Vince?

09:27.108 --> 09:30.987
I picked up my vegetables, and
now I'm having a little
libation before I go home.

09:31.028 --> 09:35.700
Well, I'd invite you to join
me, but then you'd get
jammed, uh, drinking on duty.

09:35.783 --> 09:39.078
Then you'd have to call your
delegate, which would have
been me in the old days...

09:39.161 --> 09:42.415
but now you'd have to call
yourself, you know what I
mean, Martinez?

09:42.498 --> 09:45.960
That's right, Vince.
But let's talk anyways.

09:46.043 --> 09:50.089
Leon, uh, give the boys
some nonalcoholic beverages
of their choosing, huh?

09:50.131 --> 09:53.259
-We're not having nothing.
-MARTINEZ: Hey, Vince.

09:53.342 --> 09:56.929
-Did you do a little joyridin'
last night?
-In what sense?

09:56.971 --> 09:59.890
In the sense of, uh,
stealing a bus and
caving the sides in...

09:59.932 --> 10:05.062
-navigating an alley where it
didn't fit?
-I'd ask for my delegate...

10:05.062 --> 10:07.940
except my delegate is
questioning me and
trying to jam me up.

10:08.024 --> 10:10.067
Nobody's looking
to jam you up, Vince.

10:10.151 --> 10:13.654
No. No, uh, element of
payback...

10:13.738 --> 10:16.741
for borrowing those quarters
from your coffee can?

10:16.782 --> 10:20.620
Why don't you just tell
us what happened, Vince,
and we'll see what we
can do about it.

10:20.703 --> 10:23.623
-What are you, an open-heart
surgeon?
-RUSSELL: Hi.

10:23.706 --> 10:26.250
-Hey, Diane.
-How you doing, Vince?

10:26.292 --> 10:29.920
Oh. You the, uh,
final matador, Russell?

10:30.004 --> 10:32.798
Drive the final lance in the
bull?

10:32.882 --> 10:35.092
Just talking to Vince
about the bus incident.

10:35.134 --> 10:39.305
-Oh.
-My father drove buses 27
years.

10:39.388 --> 10:41.390
Is that right?
My uncle drove.

10:41.474 --> 10:44.352
My father drove 27 years...

10:44.435 --> 10:46.562
then keeled over dead
of a heart attack.

10:46.604 --> 10:48.731
Thank God not behind the wheel.

10:49.899 --> 10:51.942
We ought to go to the house,
Vince.

10:52.026 --> 10:54.278
You want to talk about last
night?

10:54.362 --> 10:58.699
An unnamed person tried to give
four passengers door-to-door
service.

10:58.783 --> 11:00.868
-Why don't we go in, Vince?
-No.

11:00.951 --> 11:02.787
-No. I'm gonna drink more.
-No.

11:02.870 --> 11:04.121
No?

11:08.959 --> 11:09.960
Vince.

11:12.672 --> 11:15.091
Come on.
Come on.

11:15.841 --> 11:18.803
All right.
I'm not under arrest.

11:18.844 --> 11:21.764
We're just gonna
talk some stuff over.

11:22.890 --> 11:24.809
Okay, Vince.

11:29.605 --> 11:32.608
♪♪

11:46.789 --> 11:48.749
-What do we got?
-Rob-assault.

11:48.833 --> 11:53.295
Victim's Sonja Hudson.
They took her to Bellevue.
She was pretty well beat
up.

11:53.337 --> 11:56.716
How do you know it's a robbery?

11:56.757 --> 12:00.469
-The place is all ransacked.
-(door opens)

12:02.263 --> 12:04.598
-(door closes)
-I got Mr. Peepers.

12:04.598 --> 12:06.726
All right,
I got the crime scene.

12:16.610 --> 12:18.612
Come on, I saw you.
Open the door.

12:19.280 --> 12:21.657
-(knocking)
-Hey.

12:24.952 --> 12:27.788
-I didn't see anything.
-No, huh?

12:27.872 --> 12:31.125
-No.
-Open the door. We'll chat
about what you didn't see.

12:31.208 --> 12:35.463
-I don't have to do that.
-You have to unless you want
your door broken down.

12:35.546 --> 12:38.549
-Talk to me through the crack.
-(sighs)

12:42.720 --> 12:46.599
-A violent crime was committed
on your neighbor.
-You don't have to tell me.

12:46.682 --> 12:49.685
I don't have to tell you, huh?
But you didn't see nothing.

12:49.769 --> 12:54.732
I've seen police coming and
going, and
I've– and I've seen Sonja taken
out on a gurney.

12:54.774 --> 12:57.485
I think you've seen a lot more
than that.
Now open this damn door.

12:57.568 --> 13:01.113
-No.
-Where's your building super?

13:01.197 --> 13:03.824
-I'm the super.
-You're the super?

13:03.908 --> 13:06.535
Open this door
before I knock it down.

13:14.293 --> 13:17.630
-What's your name?
-Steven Cameron.

13:17.713 --> 13:20.466
-Steven, you're coming to the
station house.
-You can't make me.

13:20.508 --> 13:22.927
Don't tell me I can't make you.

13:22.968 --> 13:26.138
Now come with me
to the station house.

13:26.222 --> 13:30.142
All right.
Just, um, be right there.

13:42.571 --> 13:44.865
-The guy saw a lot.
-He said that?

13:44.949 --> 13:50.287
More or less. Let's go.
Come on, Steven. Let's go.

13:57.378 --> 14:01.757
-I'm coming on my own volition,
and I-I can leave when I want.
-Sure.

14:11.642 --> 14:14.645
♪♪

14:25.030 --> 14:27.616
I-I know I am entitled to a
counsel.

14:27.700 --> 14:30.578
Why do you think you need one?

14:30.619 --> 14:34.248
Because I– I-I don't
intend to– to let you...

14:34.290 --> 14:39.128
badger me into– into doing
something against my better
interests.

14:39.211 --> 14:42.548
Why is that? Because you
committed a crime? Huh? Is that
it?

14:43.632 --> 14:45.676
What do you like,
Steven or Steve?

14:45.718 --> 14:49.305
That depends on–
on who I'm talking to.

14:49.346 --> 14:51.348
Steve all right from me?

14:51.390 --> 14:53.642
Yeah. You know,
I mean, if you prefer.

14:53.684 --> 14:56.937
Steve, we'll be
on a lot better footing...

14:56.979 --> 14:59.732
you let me
ask my own questions.

14:59.815 --> 15:02.234
Sure, 'cause you're
the tough cop, right?

15:04.445 --> 15:06.655
Did you commit a crime?

15:08.616 --> 15:10.117
No.

15:11.911 --> 15:16.040
Steve, if you're saying
that you're a witness–

15:16.123 --> 15:20.002
Steve, you know it's your
responsibility
to come forward as a citizen...

15:20.044 --> 15:22.421
Stevie boy, Stevie,
hey, huh, Stevie boy?

15:22.504 --> 15:26.842
That's an interesting thing
you do there, Steve. You must
be a real big hit at parties.

15:26.884 --> 15:30.179
You're not gonna make me
help you with something
could get me killed...

15:30.220 --> 15:33.140
or badly injured
or badly beaten, so–

15:33.223 --> 15:35.225
But you were a witness.

15:35.309 --> 15:37.728
Yeah, but don't put–
don't– don't put–

15:38.771 --> 15:41.357
Don't put words
in my mouth 'cause–

15:41.440 --> 15:43.359
We're not gonna put words
in your mouth, Steve...

15:43.442 --> 15:46.528
and we're not gonna put a fist
in your mouth and knock you
across the room...

15:46.570 --> 15:48.906
and have you spittin'
your teeth out like Chiclets.

15:48.989 --> 15:52.785
-We're not gonna do that.
-When we were in our locker
room just now, Steve...

15:52.868 --> 15:57.039
my partner says to me, uh,
“I think this super really
wants to cooperate.

15:57.039 --> 15:59.708
He's just a little afraid.”

15:59.750 --> 16:03.837
It's no crime
in being afraid, Steve.

16:03.879 --> 16:06.840
Especially if you've seen
something
that shakes you up inside.

16:09.093 --> 16:12.888
But now-now I have two–
my two new friends, right?

16:12.930 --> 16:18.060
So, I don't– I don't have to
be afraid no more.

16:18.102 --> 16:21.772
'Cause the rapist, the one at
large...

16:21.855 --> 16:24.108
once I tell you who he is...

16:25.943 --> 16:28.320
no– no chance
he don't go to jail.

16:28.404 --> 16:33.033
Right? Wind up back out on
the streets looking to hurt me.

16:33.075 --> 16:35.077
Right?

16:37.079 --> 16:41.041
I mean, there's no chance,
right, good buddies?

16:48.382 --> 16:51.260
Gary Wilder.

16:51.301 --> 16:54.722
B3.
(sighs)

16:56.348 --> 16:58.600
The other building
I'm the super at.

17:06.775 --> 17:09.069
-Hey, Gina.
-Hey.

17:09.111 --> 17:11.113
Let's talk in the coffee room,
Vince.

17:11.196 --> 17:13.323
Sure. Make it as public
as you can.

17:13.407 --> 17:16.785
-I'll be in in just a second.
-Yeah, while you run me down
for Fancy, right, Medavoy?

17:16.827 --> 17:18.787
Let's just get some coffee now,
Vince, all right?

17:20.122 --> 17:22.166
What's that?

17:24.752 --> 17:27.004
Vince Gotelli in a huge jackpot.

17:27.087 --> 17:29.339
He's who stole the bus?

17:29.381 --> 17:32.926
Driver steps off to piss,
Vince has had a few...

17:33.010 --> 17:34.928
I guess upset with
his health problems...

17:35.012 --> 17:37.514
decides he'll give the
passengers
door-to-door service.

17:37.514 --> 17:39.850
-Who knows about it?
-Nobody, boss.

17:39.933 --> 17:42.352
Did Telli show his shield
to get on?

17:42.394 --> 17:44.772
Driver made no mention of that.

17:44.813 --> 17:46.690
MEDAVOY:
We gotta bring I.A.B. in?

17:46.774 --> 17:50.194
Let me have the driver's name.
I'll see where it stands with
his supervisor.

17:50.277 --> 17:52.613
He's two months short
of 30 years, boss.

17:52.654 --> 17:56.700
-I don't need you telling me
that, Greg.
-Excuse me. Point taken.

17:56.784 --> 17:58.869
Is he sober enough
to give a statement?

17:58.952 --> 18:02.456
-We'll walk him through that.
-All right, take it, but don't
file it.

18:11.215 --> 18:12.883
I have a clean record.

18:12.966 --> 18:15.385
We put you through our
computer, Gary,
so we know that's true.

18:15.469 --> 18:18.305
Plus, if we didn't know it,
that's the 17th time you told
us.

18:18.388 --> 18:22.935
I'd like to know why someone
knocked out with
a migraine can be dragged out
of his bed...

18:23.018 --> 18:26.188
-without even knowing why
you want to talk to him.
-Ever happen with you, Gary...

18:26.271 --> 18:29.983
right off meeting someone,
you feel like he's a lying sack
of crap?

18:31.860 --> 18:35.322
You see any radio cars outside
your building this morning?

18:35.364 --> 18:37.950
You mean police cars?

18:38.826 --> 18:41.203
Police cars, right.

18:41.286 --> 18:44.832
I heard sirens. I was lying in
my bed
with the shades drawn.

18:44.873 --> 18:48.585
-Knocked out by your migraine?
-There was a robbery across
the street.

18:48.669 --> 18:51.713
Like I said, I–
I didn't see anything.

18:51.797 --> 18:54.299
Our thought was more you did it.

18:57.636 --> 19:00.597
-Well, you're wrong.
-If you did do it, Gary...

19:00.639 --> 19:03.100
which your photo's been picked
out
by several different
witnesses...

19:03.142 --> 19:06.687
-you're in a better way than
you deserve.
-Woman's gonna recover.

19:06.770 --> 19:10.065
You plead to the robbery,
probably do three years.

19:10.107 --> 19:13.402
I had a migraine, so I didn't
do anything.
Now I want a lawyer.

19:13.402 --> 19:16.238
Didn't have a migraine,
you'd have done it?

19:19.408 --> 19:21.451
Hope that didn't make
your headache worse.

19:29.209 --> 19:32.171
-Twitch super's in 3?
-Yeah. I'll put a photo array
together.

19:32.254 --> 19:36.008
One thing I don't want, he
throws up
on my shoes off his nervousness.

19:43.056 --> 19:46.351
-Hey.
-Hi.

19:46.435 --> 19:48.353
What's Gotelli doing in?

19:48.437 --> 19:51.648
-Uh, he hijacked that bus.
-What?

19:51.732 --> 19:55.152
-Yeah.
