38:51.787 --> 38:54.623
Look, that's what they want.
Don't let it happen.

38:56.959 --> 38:59.962
-Huh. That Little Dutch Boy.
-Andy.

39:04.925 --> 39:07.470
Oh, man.

39:07.553 --> 39:10.473
We're making an official request
to talk to you, Detective.

39:10.556 --> 39:12.808
Refusal results in disciplinary
action.

39:14.810 --> 39:18.522
Me having the right
to counsel how I do...

39:18.564 --> 39:22.068
I'll peruse the yellow
pages for a lawyer and
I'll get in touch.

39:24.070 --> 39:28.199
-Same for you, Detective.
-Well, I want to use Andy's
when he's done.

39:28.240 --> 39:31.202
Might be a little delay.

39:35.206 --> 39:38.501
-What's that about, Bob?
-It's about him getting screwed
and the job don't help him–

39:38.584 --> 39:41.295
-Don't do that.
-They need him to take his
screwing privately...

39:41.379 --> 39:43.923
-and he's gonna go
along with it.
-You want to put this guy
in the system?

39:43.964 --> 39:46.967
Meaning you want me
out of your way?

39:47.051 --> 39:49.804
Nice working with you.

39:51.764 --> 39:54.350
Anyways, I hope it
all works out.

39:54.433 --> 39:55.518
Yeah.

39:59.230 --> 40:02.733
You know, I think you
should spend the night
with your mom.

40:02.775 --> 40:05.444
Tell me you don't want to
be with me. Don't tell me
where to go.

40:05.528 --> 40:08.614
I don't want to be with you.

40:08.656 --> 40:10.658
I got to figure this thing out.

40:35.141 --> 40:36.684
How do you feel, Vince?

40:36.767 --> 40:39.979
Terrible, long-term
and immediately.

40:40.062 --> 40:44.066
I know about your
health situation. Is
that what you mean by
long-term?

40:44.150 --> 40:46.777
Long-term coronary artery
disease.

40:46.819 --> 40:50.448
Plus I'm hungover,
and I'm humiliated for what I
did...

40:50.489 --> 40:53.659
wedging that bus in the alley.

40:53.742 --> 40:56.328
Here's where things stand.

40:56.370 --> 40:59.540
The driver's supervisor
understands
this case probably isn't gonna
clear.

40:59.623 --> 41:02.084
-Meaning he knows a cop's
involved.
-Whatever the reason...

41:02.168 --> 41:04.336
I don't think he's gonna
push us to get a clearance.

41:04.420 --> 41:09.884
Oh, Lieu. Hey. Oh, my God.
You don't know how
grateful I am.

41:09.967 --> 41:12.595
-Vince–
-I hope that don't mean his
driver's gonna get jammed up.

41:12.678 --> 41:15.055
Vince, will you let me speak my
piece?

41:15.097 --> 41:17.433
I'm sorry.
I'm-I'm just so relieved.

41:21.061 --> 41:23.022
You gotta retire.

41:25.191 --> 41:27.526
Oh, boy.

41:27.610 --> 41:30.154
I know you're just
two months short of 30 years.

41:30.196 --> 41:33.240
Oh, I mean, I retire now,
it's a whole different pension
package.

41:33.324 --> 41:38.871
Your heart disease. It's a
job-related
disability. You'll get
three-quarters.

41:38.954 --> 41:41.749
The money isn't taxable.

41:41.832 --> 41:45.544
-On the numbers, it's a better
deal.
-I hate admitting I'm sick.

41:45.586 --> 41:50.174
But you are sick, Vince.
And you're out of choices.

41:50.257 --> 41:54.303
-Maybe that's why you stole
that bus.
-You want me off this job?

41:54.386 --> 41:56.597
I don't, Vince, no.

41:56.639 --> 41:58.933
But we both know it's time.

42:01.060 --> 42:02.853
I need your papers in.

42:04.021 --> 42:07.274
-Today?
-Yeah.

42:11.987 --> 42:17.034
I hate for it to end,
especially like this.
I did a decent job.

42:17.076 --> 42:20.496
-Now people are gonna think
I'm a bad person.
-No. No, they won't.

42:20.579 --> 42:23.916
You want to feel that people
take circumstances into
account...

42:23.958 --> 42:26.043
but you're never sure they do.

42:30.756 --> 42:32.675
Lieu, would you excuse me?

42:34.009 --> 42:37.680
-I just need a minute.
-Yeah. Sure.

42:47.314 --> 42:48.524
(sobs)

43:18.387 --> 43:21.390
♪♪
